    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> <br>
I want to use this deck on territorial, help me to improve it.<br>
<br>
-4xAragorn and Prancing Pony because I really need Aragorn quickly.<br>
-3xFlaming Brand: meta choice. 3xFlaming Brand is huge against Nazguls, and they&#39;re very popular in my area.<br>
-Asfaloth: he is very good against Uruk-Hai. They usually uses Ettenmoors and Hollin. Both of them are plains, so Arwen can be power 12 :)<br>
-Rumil, Orophin and the other elves are useful when I&#39;m moving from 4 to 6 especially with Thor&#39;s Map and Lothlorien Woods.<br>
-With Gift of The Boats I can run from 6 to 9. Try to save Orophin and Rumil, PATHS, and the most important Ranger&#39;s Versatility. With 2 Ranger&#39;s Versatility triple move is possible even against Uruk-Hai or Nazgul.<br>
-Try to discard your deck before you get to site 6. That&#39;s why I use Moria Orcs. Cave Troll is good against non-versatilitys decks and can hurt your opponent a little. With Goblin Armory and Goblin Runner you can easily drop him at site 4.<br>
-Breeland Forest: this site can be very useful against hardcore Hobbit decks, if you are lucky maybe you will kill one of them.<br>
-Pillars of the Kings instead of Shores of Nen Hithoel is here because I wanna run from 6 to 9. Pillars gives only 6 twilight and can&#39;t stop me by dropping 5 orcs.<br>
-Tol Brandir: it&#39;s a _river_, I can use here RA. That&#39;s All<br>
<br>
Sorry, for my English. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=23922"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=23922" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
